Package es.ull.iis.simulation.core.flow

Classes required to define workflows

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ANDJoinFlow A MergeFlow which allows only one of the incoming branches to pass.
ConditionalFlow A MultipleSuccessorFlow whose successors are conditioned, that is, the successor can only be activated if certain condition is met.
DiscriminatorFlow An ANDJoinFlow which allows only the first true incoming branch to pass.
DoWhileFlow A StructuredLoopFlow which resembles a do-while loop.
ExclusiveChoiceFlow A ConditionalFlow which allows only one of the outgoing branches to be activated.
FinalizerFlow A Flow which finishes an execution branch.
Flow The process an element has to carry out.
ForLoopFlow A StructuredLoopFlow which resembles a for loop.
InitializerFlow A Flow which begins an execution branch.
InterleavedParallelRoutingFlow A StructuredFlow which contains a set of activities which must be performed according to a predefined set of partial orderings.
InterleavedRoutingFlow A StructuredFlow whose initial step is a ParallelFlow and whose final step is a SynchronizationFlow.
JoinFlow A FinalizerFlow which merges several incoming branches into a single one.
MergeFlow A JoinFlow which merges several incoming branches into a single outgoing branch.
MultiChoiceFlow A ConditionalFlow which allows all outgoing branches which meet their condition to be activated.
MultiMergeFlow An ORJoinFlowCreates an OR flow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
MultipleSuccessorFlow A SplitFlow with multiple successors.
ORJoinFlow A MergeFlow flow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
ParallelFlow A MultipleSuccessorFlow which creates a new work thread per outgoing branch.
PartialJoinFlow An ANDJoinFlow which allows only the n-st true incoming branch to pass.
PredefinedStructuredFlow A StructuredFlow with predefined both entry and exit points.
ProbabilitySelectionFlow A MultipleSuccessorFlow which selects one outgoing branch among a set of them by using a probability value.
SimpleMergeFlow An ORJoinFlow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
SingleFlow A Flow which executes an Activity.
SingleSuccessorFlow A Flow with a unique successor.
SplitFlow An InitializerFlow which can create several outgoing branches.
StaticPartialJoinMultipleInstancesFlow Meets the Static Partial Join for Multiple Instances pattern (WFP34) if acceptValue > 1 and acceptValue < nInstances.
StructuredDiscriminatorFlow A StructuredFlow whose initial step is a ParallelFlow and whose final step is a DiscriminatorFlow.
StructuredFlow A Flow which can contain other flows.
StructuredLoopFlow A StructuredFlow which defines a repetitive subflow.
StructuredPartialJoinFlow A StructuredFlow whose initial step is a ParallelFlow and whose final step is a PartialJoinFlow.
StructuredSynchroMergeFlow A StructuredFlow whose initial step is a MultiChoiceFlow and whose final step is a SynchronizationFlow.
SynchronizationFlow An ANDJoinFlow which passes only when all the incoming branches have been activated once.
SynchronizedMultipleInstanceFlow Meets the Multiple Instances with a Priori Design-Time Knowledge pattern (WFP13)
TaskFlow A Flow which executes some kind of work.
ThreadMergeFlow An ANDJoinFlow which merges a specified amount of work threads.
ThreadSplitFlow A SplitFlow which creates several instances of the current work thread.
WhileDoFlow A StructuredLoopFlow which resembles a while-do loop.
